    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>LOCAL VOTES ON ARENA</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By John Holl</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Holl, John</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Voters in Fairfield, Roseland, Verona and Cedar Grove are expected to vote on nonbinding referendums on November 5 ballot on whether to support using Essex County, NJ, tax revenue to help build $355 million arena in Newark for Devils and Nets (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Four Essex County municipalities -- Fairfield, Roseland, Verona and Cedar Grove -- will place nonbinding referendums on the Nov. 5 ballot that will let residents indicate whether they support using county tax dollars to help build a $355 million arena in Newark. Governor McGreevey and the YankeeNets, owners of the Devils and Nets, reached an agreement on $185 million in publicly financed bonds earlier this year to build an arena for those teams, but the State Legislature has yet to approve the plan.</p>
        <p>John Holl</p>
      </block>
